msg: implemented option to specific a specific entity should NOT be checked; no columns are to be updated and ignore any warning about fields, relations, keys, etc. This is useful when an entity is defined based on a database view; the view may not (or probably will not) appear in the table meta data and any attempt to auto-create the entity will (or should) fail.
